The paper deals with distributed computing and graph algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on symmetry breaking problems and graph algorithms also suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's use of randomized algorithms and analysis of graph properties such as arboricity and degeneracy may also make it relevant to cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture).
